<time>1417017966800</time><Rating>1< /Rating><text>2 years and $2520 later we are finally free of Massage Envy!

Wife and I visited this massage envy on Christmas vacation two years ago. An employee told us that if we signed up for memberships we could cancel them anytime within the first 30 days. Well, we weren't impressed with the massages so we did attempt to cancel them several days later. We were told that there is no 30-day cancellation policy and that no employee would have told us otherwise.

Because we were on vacation our memberships had to be transferred to Washington, which later came back to bite us as well. The local shop didn't have all our records, so their record of our 'months served' was different from the actual payments we had made. Unfortunately we were not diligent about arguing with them on this point, and we ended up paying for around 18 months instead of 12. We also had our accounts frozen for 6 months, yielding the grand total time served at 24 months.

Finally, please note that the monthly membership does not include tip to the therapist. The therapist's wage assumes that tips will be made, so there is an ethical obligation to pay $10-$20 per 'free massage'. I make no comment as to whether this is fair, but it is something to budget for when considering the total cost of the membership (and something that we initially overlooked).<//text><Pics>None<//Pics>< Resp>

<time>1620654942369<//time><Rate>3<//Rate>< text>
I like it because it's local but it's expensive compared to other beauty supplies and they don't allow returns or exchanges..

I don't like doing business anywhere I can't return or at least exchange an item... I bought hair for braiding that I ended up not being able to use because my braider said it would cut her fingers....It was never opened and I had the receipt and they wouldn't let me bring it back so I'm stuck with five packs of hair that I can never use...

If it was a wig or something I could see, but something in a package that has clearly never been opened you should at least be able to exchange!

This is a policy that is typical of a lot of Asian Merchants which is why I don't do swap meets and don't really like to patronize them because it's not the American way...

So due to their no exchange policy, I will not be shopping there again..</text>

<text>I've been searching for a wig store around my house for a while now and decided just go in here on a whim. Man, I'm so glad I did!! Instead of just telling me no they didn't have that, they actually took the time to look for some wigs that were similar. Despite not being a bright yellow, they ended up showing me one that I really loved so I went ahead and purchased it! <review>I had a pretty horrible experience with this location.  Firstly, there was some good to be had with the company itself.  The truck was almost new and therefore in good condition.  After the use of the truck, I had a billing issue which took a few calls to customer service; all of those people were enthusiastic, helpful and polite.  Return to a local drop off spot was super easy and staffed by a nice guy.  I kept my part of the deal with gas, etc., so no unexpected charges afterwards.

But my experience at this location was enormously off-putting.  The man who assumed responsibility for helping me was enormously rude.  I'm waiting to speak to someone at a desk when I hear this guy standing 20 feet behind me ask "what do you need?"  There were no lights on this day because of an electrical blackout on the block, so I couldn't see his eyes.  Given that I was next to another person waiting and that he did not address anyone (sir, ma'am, or even a "hey, you"), I asked to whom he was speaking.  He tells me, and this is word for word, "I'm talking to you.  Come here.  If I'm going to talk to you I need you here, not standing over there."  This in the most arrogant tone imaginable. < Review>
This is the best UHaul location on the West Side, hands down. I've had to rent a UHaul more than once in LA over the last few years and have gone to a few different places now. This time, I went out of my way to rent from these guys because the difference in customer service is night and day. I wasn't disappointed, and they even let me off the hook on a few things they definitely could have hit me with a fee for.

The folks who work there are super relaxed, know their craft well, and work well within their team to get you in, registered, out to the lot, and out the gate. Literally everyone who works there is cool, and it's always a pleasure rather than a horror story to rent from these guys.

Biggest thumbs up I can give. I highly recommend going out of your way on moving day to simplify things and work with these folks.</Review>

<review>Fuddruckers has been my go to place since I was a kid. I always loved it. It's one of the only places I know that serves melted cheese as a dipping sauce. So I always get the chicken strips just like when I was a kid and dip it into that cheese. Man it's good.

This restaurant is a little small and they don't have any booths so be prepared to sit in soft padded chairs. It's not too small though but compared to the others it's a small location. The food is always good as to be expected. The arcade is also small with very few games but it's enough to keep the kids happy.

To those who have never came and don't know what to get I would recommend the hangover burger.</review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNQveukOPV7OVgOjyNhhPa2XwiRgO8NX1zRfVdI=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</Pictures>< Response>

<Resp>None<//Resp><UserId.>105353389161113428804< /UserId.><Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
Been a decade since I've had a Fuddruckers burger.  Definitely will eat at Fuddruckers more often.  Bbq burger had much flavor.
No one cooks a burger the way I like aside from myself.  I grill everything on charcoal on the rare occasions I am home.
The 1/2 lb. burger I had here today wasn't charcoal grilled, but cooked to perfection, "medium rare".  Just dripping with grease, seasoned just right, and probably the best burger I've had in quite awhile.
Thinking about taking a walk back over there right now from my hotel for another.

Great burgers, topping bar, and a good price.  5 star from this guy.</review>

<rate>4</rate>< review>
Always a fun experience here. Enough games for the kids but not too many. Good music. Love the build your own bars and fresh toppings. Always plenty of seating.

Wait times to order food can be a little slow, consider going before or after rush hours.

Food is made to order and above average, but nothing to write home about. Be careful ordering a buffalo burger, it's definitely NOT buffalo chicken in a bun, it's REAL buffalo meat!

We'll be back, overall fun experience.</review>

<review>The food was great. The location itself needs a renovation.

I really like the burgers and the shakes and fries are good too. They have an ice cream bar, those touchscreen soda machies, and even a little arcade.

Basically, you order your burger (beef, chicken, deer, buffalo, or fish--can't remember if fish was an option), they give you a buzzer that goes off when your food is ready, you pick up your food, take it to the condiments bar to add your choice of lettuces, tomato, onions, ketchup, mayonnaise, mustard, etc.<//review><Response>None<//Response><gmapID>0x80dd2bea49624ac5:0x4165ec6597791444< /gmapID>< pics>

<Review>Stopped by here with my wife and her sister on the way to the Long Beach airport.  Both of the girls ordered their burgers medium well and I ordered mine well done specifically telling her no pink.  When we get our burgers mine is rare and the girls burgers were well done.

I went up front and asked for the manager.  I explained to her the situation but told her that I was going to eat it anyway because we were really tight on time because of a flight.  She was adamant about making another one and it would only take a few minutes.  I was ok with it as long as it was really quick and I went on to tell her what kind of burger it was just in case.

Fifteen minutes went by so I decided to go up and see what was going on.  She said the burger was almost finished.  I waited there and she finally gave me the burger which wasn't even the right one.  So after all of that I had to wait even longer for the right burger.  This was the manager I was dealing with and she had no clue how to handle this properly.

Once I got the food it was good but the whole situation was ridiculous.  That manager shouldn't be there.  I won't be going back there ever again.<//Review><rating>1<//rating><user_id>110581213894131225381< /user_id><Pics>None<//Pics>< gmap_id>

<username>Chris R</username>< Text>
Stopped by here with my wife and her sister on the way to the Long Beach airport.  Both of the girls ordered their burgers medium well and I ordered mine well done specifically telling her no pink.  When we get our burgers mine is rare and the girls burgers were well done.

I went up front and asked for the manager.  I explained to her the situation but told her that I was going to eat it anyway because we were really tight on time because of a flight.  She was adamant about making another one and it would only take a few minutes.  I was ok with it as long as it was really quick and I went on to tell her what kind of burger it was just in case.

Fifteen minutes went by so I decided to go up and see what was going on.  She said the burger was almost finished.  I waited there and she finally gave me the burger which wasn't even the right one.  So after all of that I had to wait even longer for the right burger.  This was the manager I was dealing with and she had no clue how to handle this properly.

Once I got the food it was good but the whole situation was ridiculous.  That manager shouldn't be there.  I won't be going back there ever again.<//Text>

<Rate>4<//Rate>< Name>
Art Holguin</Name>
<userid>109152277596660699868</userid><Gmap_id>0x80dd2bea49624ac5:0x4165ec6597791444<//Gmap_id><Pictures>None< /Pictures></record>

<user_id>110828766331666743367< /user_id><user_name>Thomas Wyatt<//user_name>< time>
1544740231202< /time>
< rate>
3< /rate>
< Review>
Let me tell you a story. Once upon a time there were Fuddruckers all around, but slowly they began to disappear. Sometime in the early 90's, I believe this was the last one left in Southern California. Despite that, they still used their butcher shop and still baked treats in the bakery/ice cream spot. The brownies were very good. Sometime in the mid '00 this changed. There was a resurgence, Fuddruckers started coming back, they even started serving venison, buffalo and ostritch. I think this is where the problem started. They stopped baking cookies and sweets, and I don't know that they still use the butcher area for anything but storage.  At some point they reduced what they have on the menu and you have what they currently serve now.  It's not much, and it's only okay.
Yes, you get to make your burger your way with the veggies and condiments. And yes you can put on as much nacho cheese on your burger and potato wedges as you want, but I find myself only coming here for the cheese and potato wedges. Parking is okay, staff is average, food is average, selection is low. Don't come here if you have fond memories. If you want a burger with a ton of nacho cheese, this is your place.</Review>
<Pictures>None<//Pictures>< Resp>
None< /Resp>

<Review>My 1st time here, and my experience was a complete disaster, I'm not going back. I ordered 2 Elk burgers with fries and drinks. After waiting 25 minutes for my order, I noticed they weren't really warm, almost as if they have been sitting in the open for a while.(not under the heat lamp). My mistake on not saying anything.

All the workers looked like high schoolers with no working/customer service skills, constantly forgetting how to properly set up the orders right before calling the customers name on the mic. Customers picking up their orders looked stressed out as if their orders were wrong.

I'm not a carnivorous person and finding out my burgers were 1/2lb patties just grossed the f out of me. Two bites and I couldn't continue, it felt like I was biting through an Elks torso. I make Elk burgers at home all the time, and I couldn't compare. Not to mention the 35 dollars for 2 burgers, 2 fries, 2 fountain drinks. This experience pissed me off, because I had just gotten off from my construction job, was hungry and tired. 101183189993115226419< /user>
<Name>cmilton111< /Name><time>1504631847204<//time><rate>4< /rate>< review>
Once again I was invited to a restaurant that I have missed. I was really surprised at all there is with this restaurant. I would give this Fuddruckers 5 Stars except for a couple of things I will briefly mention at the end of this review.

First, I love to order my burger; cooked the way I like it (1/2 pound for me was very good). The burger is cooked and then I get to add all the things to it that makes my burger perfect. Lots of extra lettuce, extra tomato, extra pickles and easy onions (they have a lot more to choose from) and of course, mayonaise, mustard, and ketchup ( lot of tasty choices). This burger is way better than the competition!

I loved the French fries that came with my Hamburger, they were very tasty; cooked perfectly!  (I am hard to please)

The Coke machine was a bit funny for me as the machine (dispenser) requires a three week course in how to use it successfully (joking).  I did figure it out. The coke was the correct ratio of syrup to bicarbonate (some machines get it all wrong).

The interior is fun; a lot of interesting elements for decor. I talked with a few people about this place and got all favorable responses. From good to very good!

I read the reviews and they are mostly favorable also. I also like that the owner or manager responded to customers. I recommend that to all business owners.. It is smart and it will bring customers back.

I did mention that I would comment on a couple of things here at the end. Two points to greatly improve this location. The front exterior is a bit in disrepair but worse than that is the dirty awning (very dirty). Sorry, but that will turn some customers away and that would be sad because this restaurant is a good dining experience. The second issue is the Men's restroom has (terrible) graffiti; some of the windows at the front door also are"tagged". Having owned a store I found that removing graffiti right away is the best policy.

Thank you for a great burger. I will return and if those issues are resolved I will raise my review the 5 Stars.

Hope this helps!

By:
cmilton111
Google Guide
8.28.2017<//review>

<user>106750980997530469627<//user>< date>
1397108460674</date>
<rating>5<//rating><pics>None<//pics>< Text>
The people behind the counter could have been more professional and it wasn't the cleanest place to eat, BUT the food was amazing! I had a turkey burger with guacamole and cheddar cheese on a wheat bun which they make on site. I added (from the bar) Romaine lettuce, tomatoes, pickles and jalapenos. Delish! The burger was cooked perfectly--thoroughly but still moist; the bun was grilled but still tender. I had the meal including sweet potato fries and a cherry vanilla Dr. Pepper (YUM!). I tried an onion ring from my friend's order and it was awesome...the batter was seasoned well; didn't need any sort of dipping sauce. My first time and comparable to 5guys! :D</Text>

< username>
Iama Techie<//username>
< Review>
Good food, decent service, clean friendly atmosphere. Although I did stand (as the only customer) for nearly two minutes without being recognized in front of 2 order takers who didn't appear to be doing anything. They might have been checking systems, or might have just changed over. Still.. a quick 'hello, I'll be right with you" is always nice to have. It was kind of embarrassing to just stand there, not sure which crew member to approach, and wait to be acknowledge. This was my first time to any Fuddruckers so I may have not been sure of the protocol. Otherwise everyone was quite friendly and I was greeted by a preparer (manager?) from back near the grill as I walked in so I felt wanted and appreciated immediately.
I like that the burger is cooked to your specification and size.
I really liked the layout of the condiments. Everything you could ask for including jalapenos and pepperchinis arranged very carefully.
Bun appeared to be fresh baked and although large, still not quite big enough for 1/2 lb burger and all the fixin's. It was delicious, but pretty messy, LOL!

I enjoyed it and will return. Although I might get the 1/3 lb next time. The 1/2 lb was huge!

= = I am a real person, this is an honest review. Please see my others for veracity = =<//Review>
